
Release notes for gst-ipcam-server 0.1

This is a release announcement for gst-ipcam-server software package

gst-ipcam-server is a media streaming server based on gstreamer and rtsp protocol and gst-rtsp-server project. The server is the implementation for SH7724 streaming server prototype. The server support 3 codecs for video channel: H.264, MPEG4 and JPEG

Current version is 0.1 with 2 components:
	* server: based on gst-rtsp-server project
	* client: a simple client used for demontrations

Feature of this release
Server:
	* use library from gst-rtsp-server project
	* support both 3 video channels, but only one can be run at the same time
	* addresses for the video stream in the video-demo application are:
		- rtsp://ip:8554/mp4 for MPEG4 channel
		- rtsp://ip:8554/h264 for H.264 channel
		- rtsp://ip:8554/jpg for JPEG channel
	* both run at 25/1 fps
	* the address can be open with a movie player like mplayer or totem movie player
Client:
	* A simple demo client with gtk ui
	* support basic features:
		- connect/disconnect
		- play/pause stream
	* support both 3 video channels
	
Git repository:
	git://github.com/trungnt/gst-ipcam-server.git

